25/08/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- A bus carrying a wedding party crashed into a retaining wall near the town of Amasya on Sunday (24 August) killing 19 people and injuring eight.
There were about 30 passengers in the vehicle when it went off the road.
Police believe that the bus may have been speeding.
In other news, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano left Turkey on Saturday.
He had spent a week at an Istanbul hospital for an operation to remove gallstones.
(AP - 24/08/03;
AFP - 23/08/03)
